<Layouts.app flash={@flash}>
  <div class="lg:grid lg:grid-cols-12 mt-5 max-w-5xl mx-auto">
    <.custom_nav active="chelekom-docs-pagination" />
    <div class="lg:col-span-10">
      <.custom_info
        title="Pagination"
        description="Phoenix LiveView pagination with page numbers, ellipses, first, last, and next, previous paginations. Supports various styles and layouts for efficient navigation of large data sets."
        mix="mix mishka.ui.gen.component pagination"
        github="https://github.com/mishka-group/mishka_chelekom/blob/master/priv/components/pagination.eex"
        tags={["Component", "Stateless", "JS-module"]}
      />
      <.custom_tab id="chelekom-pagination-tab">
        <:documentation_panel>
          <.heading2 class="mb-5" id="overview">
            <.link patch={~p"/chelekom/docs/pagination/#overview"}>
              Overview of the Phoenix LiveView Pagination Component
            </.link>
          </.heading2>

          <.cp>
            The
            <strong>
              Mishka Chelekom Pagination
            </strong>
            component is a highly flexible and customizable <strong>Phoenix LiveView</strong>
            tool designed for paginated navigation. It's perfect for large datasets or multi-page content, supporting both numerical and <.custom_inline_code>first/last</.custom_inline_code>,
            <.custom_inline_code>next/previous</.custom_inline_code>
            navigation.
          </.cp>

          <.custom_code_wrapper elements_class="space-y-5">
            <.pagination total={@posts.total} active={@posts.active} size="small" />
            <.pagination
              total={@posts.total}
              active={@posts.active}
              variant="transparent"
              color="natural"
              size="small"
            />
            <.pagination
              total={@posts.total}
              active={@posts.active}
              color="natural"
              variant="subtle"
              size="small"
            />
          </.custom_code_wrapper>

          <.cp margin="mt-5">
            This
            <strong>
              <.link
                title="Phoenix LiveView component"
                class="transition-colors hover:text-[#448D96]"
                navigate={~p"/chelekom"}
              >
                Phoenix LiveView component
              </.link>
            </strong>
            offers dynamic pagination states such as current, disabled, and ellipses for skipped pages, making navigation intuitive and user-friendly, even with large datasets.
          </.cp>

          <.custom_block position="left" color="success" class="my-8" border="medium">
            <.cp>
              By using the class prop, you can apply custom classes or Tailwind CSS classes to customize the appearance and behavior of the components, allowing for flexible design changes.
            </.cp>
          </.custom_block>

          <.heading2 margin="my-5" id="padination-js-modules">
            <.link patch={~p"/chelekom/docs/pagination/#padination-js-modules"}>
              About LiveView JS module commands
            </.link>
          </.heading2>

          <.cp class="my-8">
            In the padination component, several attributes allow users to execute custom LiveView JS commands based on interactions. These attributes are:
          </.cp>

          <ul>
            <li>
              <strong>on_select:</strong>
              This attribute allows for a custom JavaScript module to run when an item is selected, enabling specific actions or animations.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>on_first:</strong>
              This attribute triggers a custom JS module when the first item is accessed, ideal for initializing states or actions.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>on_last:</strong>
              This attribute runs a custom JavaScript module when the last item is reached, enhancing user feedback or navigation.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>on_next:</strong>
              This attribute defines a JS module that executes when navigating to the next item, allowing for smooth transitions.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>on_previous:</strong>
              This attribute allows for a custom JavaScript module to run when navigating to the previous item, facilitating additional interactions.
            </li>
          </ul>
          <.cp class="my-8">
            These attributes empower developers to create dynamic, engaging experiences tailored to user needs.
          </.cp>

          <.heading2 margin="my-5" id="base-pagination">
            <.link patch={~p"/chelekom/docs/pagination/#base-pagination"}>
              Base variant
            </.link>
          </.heading2>

          <.custom_code_wrapper elements_class="text-sm" code_class="text-xs" code={@code_22}>
            <.pagination total={@posts.total} active={@posts.active} size="small" />
          </.custom_code_wrapper>

          <.heading2 margin="my-5" id="default-variant-pagination">
            <.link patch={~p"/chelekom/docs/pagination/#default-variant-pagination"}>
              Default variant of Phoenix LiveView pagination component
            </.link>
          </.heading2>

          <.cp>
            The default variant of the
            <.link navigate={~p"/chelekom/docs/pagination"}>Mishka Chelekom pagination</.link>
            automatically applies a solid background and border that change on hover, ideal for primary actions. With just a single prop, you can choose from a variety of colors, making it easy to adapt to different design needs while offering a flexible, visually appealing solution for any interface.
          </.cp>
          <.custom_code_wrapper
            elements_class="[&>*]:mb-4 text-sm"
            code_class="text-xs"
            code={@code_1}
          >
            <.pagination
              total={@posts.total}
              active={@posts.active}
              size="small"
              variant="default"
              color="natural"
            />
